Create playbook that takes 
	1. username 
	2. public key
 from user and creates that user on all the instances you have. Make sure the same playbook allows to remove the users from the system 
Docs are here
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/modules/user_module.html
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/playbooks_prompts.html
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/playbooks_tags.html

Create a playbook that installs wordpress on 1 of the instances out of all instances you have on AWS. It should install all the necessary packages of wordpress including mysql/mariadb. The playbook should also add the following users to a system 
	1. Bob 
	2. ben 
	3. lisa
	4. katty
		a. with ssh keys generated automatically
Playbook should start wordpress and create route53 record automatically for:
wordpress.yourdomain.com. Once the tasks completed send a link to your wordpress in  a group. 